---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Bulk File Downloader"
  description="Privacy Policy for Bulk File Downloader Chrome extension. We respect your privacy and do not collect any personal data."
>
  <!-- Navigation -->
  <nav class="nav">
    <div class="container nav-content">
      <a href="/" class="nav-brand">
        <img src="/icon128.png" alt="Bulk File Downloader" class="nav-logo" />
        <span class="nav-title">Bulk File Downloader</span>
      </a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/#features">Features</a>
        <a href="/#how-it-works">How It Works</a>
        <a href="/#faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="#" class="nav-cta">Add to Chrome</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="privacy-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="privacy-header">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-content">
        <section class="privacy-section">
          <h2>Overview</h2>
          <p>
            Bulk File Downloader is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains
            how the Bulk File Downloader Chrome extension handles your information. The short version:
            <strong>we don't collect, store, or transmit any of your personal data.</strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="privacy-section">
          <h2>Information We Don't Collect</h2>
          <p>Bulk File Downloader does <strong>not</strong> collect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Personal information (name, email, address, etc.)</li>
            <li>Browsing history or activity</li>
            <li>Information about the websites you visit</li>
            <li>Files you download or their contents</li>
            <li>Analytics or usage data</li>
            <li>IP addresses or location data</li>
            <li>Any other form of tracking information</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="privacy-section">
          <h2>How the Extension Works</h2>
          <p>
            Bulk File Downloader operates entirely within your browser. Here's how it works:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Active Tab Permission:</strong> The extension only accesses webpage content
              when you click the extension icon. It cannot access any page unless you explicitly
              activate it.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Page Scanning:</strong> When activated, the extension scans the current page's
              HTML for downloadable file links. This scanning happens locally in your browser—no
              data is sent anywhere.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Downloads:</strong> When you choose to download files, the extension uses
              Chrome's built-in downloads API to save files directly to your computer. We don't
              intercept or monitor these downloads.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="privacy-section">
          <h2>Permissions Explained</h2>
          <p>The extension requests these Chrome permissions:</p>
          <div class="permission-list">
            <div class="permission-item">
              <span class="permission-name">activeTab</span>
              <span class="permission-desc">
                Allows the extension to access the current tab only when you click on the
                extension icon. This is the most privacy-respecting way to access page content.
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="permission-item">
              <span class="permission-name">downloads</span>
              <span class="permission-desc">
                Required to save files to your computer using Chrome's download manager.
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="privacy-section">
          <h2>Data Storage</h2>
          <p>
            Bulk File Downloader does not store any data locally or remotely. Each time you use
            the extension, it starts fresh with no memory of previous sessions. Your downloaded
            files are saved to your computer through Chrome's standard download process.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="privacy-section">
          <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            Bulk File Downloader does not use any third-party services, analytics platforms,
            or external servers. The extension operates completely offline after installation.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="privacy-section">
          <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our extension does not collect any personal information from anyone, including
            children under 13 years of age.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="privacy-section">
          <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            If we make changes to this Privacy Policy, we will update the "Last updated" date
            at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="privacy-section">
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or the Bulk File Downloader
            extension, please reach out through the Chrome Web Store listing.
          </p>
        </section>

        <div class="privacy-summary">
          <h3>Summary</h3>
          <p>
            Bulk File Downloader is designed with privacy in mind. We believe you should be able
            to use helpful browser tools without sacrificing your privacy. That's why we've built
            an extension that works entirely on your device without collecting or transmitting any data.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="back-link">
        <a href="/">← Back to Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="footer-content">
        <div class="footer-brand">
          <img src="/icon128.png" alt="Bulk File Downloader" class="footer-logo" />
          <span class="footer-title">Bulk File Downloader</span>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-links">
          <a href="/#features">Features</a>
          <a href="/#how-it-works">How It Works</a>
          <a href="/#faq">FAQ</a>
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-copy">
          © {new Date().getFullYear()} Bulk File Downloader. All rights reserved.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Navigation */
  .nav {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    padding: 16px 0;
    background: rgba(13, 13, 13, 0.95);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
  }

  .nav-content {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }

  .nav-brand {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .nav-logo {
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
  }

  .nav-title {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--white);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .nav-links {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 32px;
  }

  .nav-links a {
    color: var(--gray-400);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .nav-links a:hover {
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .nav-cta {
    background: var(--orange);
    color: var(--dark) !important;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .nav-cta:hover {
    background: var(--orange-light);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .nav-links {
      display: none;
    }
  }

  /* Privacy Page */
  .privacy-page {
    padding: 140px 0 80px;
    min-height: calc(100vh - 200px);
  }

  .privacy-header {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .privacy-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--gray-600);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .privacy-content {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .privacy-section {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .privacy-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--white);
    padding-bottom: 8px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-800);
  }

  .privacy-section p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .privacy-section ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .privacy-section li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .privacy-section li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 10px;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    background: var(--orange);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .privacy-section strong {
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .permission-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 16px;
  }

  .permission-item {
    background: var(--dark-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-800);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 20px;
  }

  .permission-name {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--orange);
    background: rgba(255, 140, 0, 0.1);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .permission-desc {
    display: block;
    color: var(--gray-400);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .privacy-summary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255, 140, 0, 0.1), transparent);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 140, 0, 0.2);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  .privacy-summary h3 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: var(--orange);
  }

  .privacy-summary p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .back-link {
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  .back-link a {
    color: var(--orange);
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  /* Footer */
  .footer {
    background: var(--gray-900);
    padding: 48px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-800);
  }

  .footer-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .footer-brand {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .footer-logo {
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
  }

  .footer-title {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .footer-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 32px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .footer-links a {
    color: var(--gray-400);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .footer-links a:hover {
    color: var(--orange);
  }

  .footer-copy {
    color: var(--gray-600);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
</style>
